<p>Why is never true returned? The given name exists in the array rows and the if(rows[i].userName == name) gets triggert, but why won't this function return true? </p>  <pre><code>function existUser(name){     var Result = false;     OOTW.MYSQL.query('SELECT * FROM Time',function(err,rows){     if(err) throw err;         for (var i = 0; i &lt; rows.length; i++) {              if (rows[i].userName == name) {                  Result = true;              }         };       });     console.log(Result);     return Result; } </code></pre>